<h2>Announcement: Submit Your Everquest Guide!</h2>&nbsp;posted&nbsp;Sunday, July 25, 2004 9:57 AM EDT (  <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/printnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/print.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Printer Friendly Page" /></a> <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/sendnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/mail.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Send this Article to a Friend" /></a> )<br />You can now submit your <b>EQ Guide</b> to us on our <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/everquest-addguide.php" class="newslink">Add Guide page</a>. Special rewards for unique and thorough guides. Please submit your personal work only, do not copy someone else's guide.<br /><br /><div align="center"><h1>EQ Everquest News</h1></div>
<br />
<h2>Don&#146;t miss out on EverQuest Newsletters or Email from SOE!</h2><br /><br>We have a few emails that will be sent out soon that you don't want to miss! Make sure you are signed up to recieve newsletters and other important emails from SOE. What's included when you sign up?<br><br>You'll receive the quarterly Newsletters for the games you are signed up for.<br>You'll receive any promotional emails that we send out<br><br>To make sure you receive the next newsletter, do the following: <br><br>Click on My Account in the Station.com header<br>Click on Email Newsletters<br>Select those you wish to receive<br>Click on Make Changes (If you aren't sure you are getting the emails, click on Make Changes even if you don't change anything, just to refresh the setting.)<br>Or you can just visit https://secure.station.sony.com/optin/viewOptins.m<br> <br>How come I never seem to get any of the emails?<br><br>There are a couple of reasons you may not be receiving the emails from SOE:<br><br>You need to update your Email Address:<br>An incorrect Email Address is a common reason for not receiving the emails from the station. To update your email address, go to My Account in the Station.com header, select Registration, update your email address, make sure the box for "Check here to receive future Station e-mails with announcements of new games, contests, and more" is checked and Accept changes.</br></br>Email sent by SOE is being blocked:</br>If your e-mail system has a block, junk, bulk, or spam mail folder, you'll want to make sure that it allows e-mail from The Station@sony.com [station-mailer@sony-online.com]. You will need to check the options, properties, or preferences of your mail system to determine how to set this up.</br></br>Options not saved:</br>There's a chance that your options were not set correctly when the system changed over to this system. To fix this, click on the [Clear-All] link and click on Make Changes. Then select your options again and click on Make Changes again. That should refresh the list.</br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Announcing the Ninth
  Official SOE Podcast!</h2><br />  <p>Tune in to the Ninth Official SOE Podcast. We hope you all enjoy the latest installment of our podcast series. Make sure to let us know how you like it! You can fire off an email to us at <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/mailto:feedback@soe.sony.com">feedback@soe.sony.com</a> or head over to the <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/station/posts/list.m?topic_id=11500000607" target=_blank>Show Notes</a> and give us your comments.<p>You can download the MP3 file directly or subscribe to the RSS feed by clicking the button listed below. We have high and low bandwidth versions of the podcast available.</p>   <a href="http://download.station.sony.com/patch/web/misc/Podcast09_128k.mp3">High-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_lrg.xml"></a> <a href="http://download.station.sony.com/patch/web/misc/Podcast09_64k.mp3">Low-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_sml.xml"></a> <p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>November Forum
  Challenge &#150; November 20, 2006</h2><br /><br> <p>This week in the US, many people will be celebrating Thanksgiving with family and eating awesome food like: turkey, ham, mashed potatoes with gravy, stuffing, pumpkin pie and lots of other good stuff. Many cultures around the world celebrate similar holidays centered on harvest time.</p> <p>The forum challenge for November is to post a recipe and picture from your culture that is used to celebrate harvest time. (It does not necessarily have to be a recipe your family serves)</p> <p>The categories for this challenge will be: </p> Most unusual recipe<br> Most appealing recipe<br> Recipe most likely to have the most leftovers if served in your house<br> <br> <p>The Harvest Challenge will start today as of this post and run through Monday, November 27th at noon PST. You may submit your recipe and picture to cdelzer@soe.sony.com. Please include your forum handle and what culture uses this recipe for its harvest celebration as well as the category you wish to submit your recipe in.</p> <p>On Monday, November 27th sometimes after noon PST, I will post the recipes on the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board?board.id=Fun">Just for Fun forum</a> and start a poll for each category so the community can vote on the recipes. One challenge winner from each category will receive a special forum title and an in-game prize for one character of their choice.</p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Tech and Account Phone
  Support Closed 11/23 and 11/24</h2><br /><br> <p>Tech and Account Phone support will be unavailable on Thursday November 23rd and Friday November 24th in observance of the holiday.</p> <p>Chat support will be available during its normal time Monday through Friday 10am through 7pm PST at station.sony.com/chat.</p> <p>Email support is always available at station.sony.com/email.</p> <p>Our Self-help knowledgebase is also available at station.sony.com/kb with answers to your questions.</p> <p>Phone support will return on Monday November 27th at its normal hours Monday through Friday 10am through 7pm PST.</p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Sony Online
  Entertainment Games Available Through T-Mobile HotSpot!</h2><br /><br> <p>Beginning today, Monday, November 20, you can download EverQuest II, EverQuest, PlanetSide, and The Matrix Online at no cost with your T-Mobile HotSpot subscription! There are two packages available to subscribers.</p> <p>Gaming Pack Offer<br> T-mobile offers new subscribers to their HotSpot service the ability to download EQ, EQII, PS, and MxO at no cost and play for up to 30 days for free.</p> <p>Gamer on the Go Offer<br> T-mobile will allow subscribers of any SOE subscription based PC game to use their HotSpot service to play SOE games for $4.99/month (does not include SOE subscription price)</p> <p>You can visit the <a target="_blank" href="https://selfcare.hotspot.t-mobile.com/accountcreate/ExternalSetPromotionCode.do?promo=SOETWB96">T-Mobile HotSpot website</a> for more information on the promotion and the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.station.sony.com/promotions/T-Mobile">SOE Station website</a> for information on games and game keys.</p> 
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge &#150; November 16, 2006</h2><br /><br>Ngreth answers tradeskillers pleas to increase stacking on some of their more commonly used tradeskill itmes. To see what will increase or to submit itmes you would like to see increased you can follow<a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&message.id=17320&view=by_date_ascending&page=1"> this thread</a>.<br><br>CurtEQ, one of the EQ programmers, let the community know that he found and fixed the Demiplane of Blood instance crashing due to charm and death. You can read more about it <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=326423#M326423">here</a>.<br><br>Maddoc talks a little bit about the Reintroduction of boats coming soon. Read what he has to say <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=325917#M325917">here</a>.<br><br>Nodyin informs the community that new hot zones have been selected and are almost ready to go. Find out more <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=325060#M325060">here</a>.<br><br>In this week's edition of <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10447&jump=true">Ky's Chatter Box</a>: How much platinum have you spent in the Shadowhaven Casino? <br><br>While walking through the forest in Lesser Faydwar you are suddenly surrounded by fairies who start pulling your hair, rifling through your backpacks and bags, untie any ties on your armor and just generally being a nuisance. You realize that if you don't do something quick these curious forest sprites will wreak total havoc on you and your equipment so you... Finish this scenarion in this week's <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10452&jump=true">Creative Writing thread</a>.
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge RiffRaff &#150; November 16, 2006</h2><br /><br> Real life first name: Mike<br> Forum handle: Skaterrat<br> Main Character name: Issack Knewton<br> Server: The Nameless<br> Guild: Euphoria<br> <br> Where in the real life world do you live? Alpharetta GA, 15min North of Atlanta<br> <br> How long have you played EQ? 5 years<br> <br> What other MMOs have you played? WOW, lineage 2<br> <br> What type of work do you do? Manufacturing<br> <br> How long is your typical gaming session when playing EQ? 4-6 hours<br> <br> What does a typical EQ day consist of for you? Raiding and finding recruits for the guild.<br> <br> What was the race and class of your very first character? Wood Elf Ranger<br> <br> What got you into gaming and what sort of games do you like the most? I been gaming since I was about 5y/o. I remember playing Pac Man with my brother, sister, and mom on the Atari VCS.<br> <br> What other hobbies or activities do you take part in, other then playing EverQuest? I play the guitar, and also like to read books.<br> <br> What is your highest level in EQ? 75 with 700+ aa and gaining aa every day<br> <br> What race and class is your main character? Dwarf Paladin<br> <br> What do you like the most about the class you have chosen for your main character? The ability to tank. Spot heal was the main reason why I created him.<br> <br> Does your main character worship a deity? Brell<br> <br> How did you choose your main character's name? At the Time, Paladins were knows as Sir, and Sir Issack Knewton fit the dwarf paladin well.<br> <br> Which classes in EQ have you NOT played? Bard<br> <br> What is your favorite expansion? POP<br> <br> What is your favorite zone? The old Veeshans Peek, before revamp and TL? Gate out was allowed.<br> <br> What is your favorite npc? Hatchet in Demi, it's such a fun event.<br> <br> Which expansion do you like the least? LOY. That expansion was pointless. I don't think I ever did any XP in any of the zones.<br> <br> Which zone do you like the least? Any zone with a AE debuff that cant be cured or blocked by a quest.<br> <br> Which npc do you like the least? Portios cat. He's a pain in the neck.<br> <br> What is the most platinum you have ever spent on purchasing a single item for one of your characters?400k<br> <br> Do you have an item you no longer use but keep around for nostalgic reasons? If so what is it and why do you keep it? Resplendent War Maul. It was the first weapon I received that was acquired by my guild. I also have every single weapon I have ever received from raids by my guild.<br> <br> What do you like best about EverQuest? The social aspect and raiding with friends, getting together and kicking butt.<br> <br> What do you get out of playing EverQuest? Relaxation from a hard day at work.<br> <br> Describe your best experience from playing EverQuest? The first time we kill a raid mob. The feeling of excitement and accomplishment.<br> <br> Do you run or work for an EverQuest Fan Site? nope.<br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Announcing
  the Eighth Official SOE Podcast!</h2><br /><br>   <p>Tune in to the Eighth Official SOE Podcast. We hope you all enjoy the latest installment of our podcast series. Make sure to let us know how you like it! You can fire off an email to us at <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/mailto:feedback@soe.sony.com">feedback@soe.sony.com</a> or <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=245130&jump=true" target=_blank>head over to the forums</a> and give us your comments.<p>You can download the MP3 file directly or subscribe to the RSS feed by clicking the button listed below. We have high and low bandwidth versions of the podcast available.</p>   <a href="http://movies.station.sony.com:7000/patch/web/misc/Podcast08_128.mp3">High-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_lrg.xml"></a> <a href="http://movies.station.sony.com:7000/patch/web/misc/Podcast08_64.mp3">Low-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_sml.xml"></a> <p> <p> To see the notes from the show, go to <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/station/posts/list.m?topic_id=11500000505">the Station Community Forums</a>. </p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge &#150; November 9, 2006</h2><br /><br>Several developers join in a discussion about a <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=322887#M322887">Frostcrypt Raid Instance video</a> created by the guild Triality on Vazaelle.<br><br>Prathun responds to Necromancers about <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&message.id=9646#M9646">pet illusions and Halloween costumes</a> & talks to Druids about the <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=10592#M10592">Barkspur duration</a>.<br><br>You turn a corner from a wooded forest into a clearing only to find yourself surrounded by a horde of Orcs. You know that there are too many to deal with yourself. How would you talk your way out of the situation? Finish this scenario and share your creative thinking in this week's edition of <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10437&jump=true">Creative Writing</a>.<br><br>In <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10434&jump=true">Ky's Chatter Box</a> share the best message you have seen in the LFG window when people are LFG.<br><br>Check out all the player highlights posted on EQPlayers since March 2006 in a nice neat list. If you would like to be highlighted, visit the Town Crier on the forums and get the questionnaire and directions <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Crier&message.id=373&jump=true">here</a>.<br><br>Read Smed's Newest blog on Station.com regarding <a href="http://blog.station.sony.com/">The Single Bullet Theory</a> and <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&message.id=5174">post your comments on the EQ Forums</a>.<br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge RiffRaff &#150; November 9, 2006</h2><br /><br> Real life first name: Joe<br> Forum handle: Waring_McMarrin<br> Main Character name: Waring McMarrin<br> Server: The Tribunal<br> Guild: The Death Squad<br> <br> Where in the real life world do you live? Virgina <br> <br> How long have you played EQ? 7 years<br> <br> What other MMOs have you played? Everquest 2, Starwars Galixys, Dark Age of Camelot, Anarchy Online, City of Hero's, World of Warcraft<br> <br> What type of work do you do? Serve in the Military <br> <br> How long is your typical gaming session when playing EQ? Play from 4 to 6 hours a session depending on whether or not its during the week or weekend and if its a raid night<br> <br> What got you into gaming and what sort of games do you like the most? Started gaming because it was something fun to do with friends back when the first Nintendo was released. Eventually I was introduced to the MMO idea and wanted to try that experience and been hooked ever since. <br> <br> What other hobbies or activities do you take part in, other then playing EverQuest? Working on advancing my education.<br> <br> What is your highest level in EQ? 70 Shaman<br> <br> What race and class is your main character? Barbarian Shaman <br> <br> What do you like the most about the class you have chosen for your main character? The fact that shaman have a lot of different roles that they can play. They can support a group in big ways with healing, slowing and buffing but are not limited to that. <br> <br> Does your main character worship a deity? The Tribunal<br> <br> Which classes in EQ have you NOT played? Have played them all at one point or another though they all haven't lasted long. <br> <br> What is your favorite expansion? Gates of Discord is my current favorite but there have been a lot of good ones.<br> <br> What is your favorite zone? Halas<br> <br> What is your favorite npc? Original PoM <br> <br> Which expansion do you like the least? Legacy of Yekasha <br> <br> Which zone do you like the least? To hard to say there are plenty of zones that I dislike certain things about but not one that sticks out above all the others.<br> <br> What is the most platinum you have ever spent on purchasing a single item for one of your characters? 200k on my Grandmaster's Frostwarded Breastplate <br> <br> Do you have an item you no longer use but keep around for nostalgic reasons? If so what is it and why do you keep it? First one that comes to my mind for this would be my Spear of Fate. I haven't used it much lately but it will always remind me of the fun that I have had while playing and what is bound to come. <br> <br> What do you like best about EverQuest? The fact that there is so much to do whether its working on content or quests or just talking to friends.<br> <br> What do you get out of playing EverQuest? Cheap entertainment :P<br> <br> Describe your best experience from playing EverQuest? Hard to just limit this to one point, I would say the best times are finishing a big quest or winning raids for the first time with my guild.
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
